        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Plum Springs. This thunderstorm was moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowling Green, Smiths Grove, Oakland, Three Forks, Hays, Sunnyside,
Pondsville, Kepler, Loving, and Tuckertown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
